<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-020" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit all ActionType references via grep (~1000+) across BFF</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-on>2026-06-28</completed-on>
    <completion-note>464 ActionType refs identified across 82 files (224 BFF + 240 tests; src/server/shared/ clean). Spec FR-10 estimate of ~1000 corrected. Largest cluster: PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs (25 hits — much will disappear in task 024 dispatch deletion). 1 unrelated-symbol gotcha flagged: InlineActionInfo.ActionType string discriminator in AnalysisChatContextResponse.cs MUST be excluded from regex. 32 lowercase "actionType" JSON property hits + SSE wire field deferred to Wave 6 (FR-21 Dataverse schema rename). SupportedActionTypes (97 refs) deferred to task 023. Audit doc at notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md drives task 021 strategy.</completion-note>
    <wave>2</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>audit, bff-api, wave-2</tags>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>W1 complete (task 010)</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-10 (preparatory)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wave 2 opens with the rename. Before touching code, enumerate every `ActionType` reference in BFF source
    + tests. The full rename (task 022) needs an accurate count, a per-file breakdown, and a list of edge
    cases (XML doc comments, string literals, JSON serialization names, attribute arguments) so the rename
    plan in task 021 can decide PR sizing and conflict-risk windows. This is read-only — no source edits.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer comfortable with large-codebase refactoring.
    Goal: produce a precise inventory of `ActionType` references so the actual rename is mechanical, not exploratory.
  </role>

  <goal>
    An audit report at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md` that contains:
    1. Total reference count (rg-driven) across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `src/server/shared/` + `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`
    2. Per-file breakdown (top 25 by hit count) — file path + count
    3. Reference categories: enum-value usages (`ActionType.AiCompletion`), type-name usages (`ActionType` in signatures), property names (`SupportedActionTypes`), string literals (`"ActionType"` in JSON), XML doc comments (`&lt;see cref="ActionType"/&gt;`)
    4. Edge cases needing manual review (JSON property names, attribute string args, log message formatting)
    5. Out-of-scope confirmations: any references in non-BFF surfaces (PCF, code-pages, scripts) that R7 explicitly does NOT rename per FR-10 scope (BFF only)
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="enum-source">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-10">Full rename across BFF only. Out-of-scope: PCF, code-pages, scripts, docs (handled in Wave 6/8).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-06">No backward compatibility — `ActionType` symbol fully replaced; no aliases, no `[Obsolete]` shim.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Audit only — does NOT introduce new components; no justification triple required for this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Read-only audit — no publish-size check required.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/refactor-planning</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The C# enum `ActionType` is a misnomer post-R7 — its values name executors, not Actions. The Action concept
      now refers strictly to the `sprk_analysisaction` entity (prompt template + schema). Renaming to `ExecutorType`
      aligns the type name with the dispatch axis. FR-10 calls the rename ~1000+ references. This audit confirms.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="010" status="must-be-complete">Wave 1 complete; AiCompletionNodeExecutor compiles + tests green so the rename has a clean baseline.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 021 consumes this audit to draft the rename plan (PR sizing, conflict windows).</item>
      <item>Task 022 executes the rename mechanically.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: audit-only task; no source modification; produces planning artifact · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-10 + plan.md Wave 2 section.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Grep enum-value usages">
      Pattern: `ActionType\.\w+` across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`, `src/server/shared/`, `tests/`.
      Capture file paths + counts. These are the bulk of references (likely 600-800).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Grep type-name usages">
      Pattern: `\bActionType\b` (whole word) across same paths.
      Capture file paths + counts; subtract enum-value usages to isolate type references (signatures, generics, params).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Grep SupportedActionTypes references">
      Pattern: `SupportedActionTypes`. These will rename to `SupportedExecutorTypes` in task 023.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Grep string literals + XML doc references">
      Pattern: `"ActionType"` (string literal) + `cref="ActionType` (XML doc). Edge cases requiring manual judgment during rename.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Confirm out-of-scope surfaces">
      Grep `src/client/`, `src/dataverse/`, `scripts/` for `ActionType` references. List but do NOT include in rename scope (FR-10 says BFF-only).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Compose audit report">
      Write `notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md` covering: total counts; per-file top 25; per-category breakdown; edge cases; out-of-scope confirmations. Target: 80-120 lines.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 020 complete; advance current-task.md to task 021.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Commit">
      Commit `notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md` with conventional message: `chore(r7/audit): catalog ActionType references for Wave 2 rename (task 020, FR-10)`.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Grep (large-scale reference enumeration)</tool>
    <tool>Read (CLAUDE.md, spec, plan)</tool>
    <tool>Write (audit report)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (git commit)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="document">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 021)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 020 ✅)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Audit report exists at notes/spikes/actiontype-audit.md</criterion>
